    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factors achieving levels below required gradations and six factors not assessed, the assessment team determined that the Monte Carlo UQ envelope conservatively bounds the clinical hemolysis threshold with 95% confidence. The UQ narrative references a screening sensitivity study identifying rotational speed and inlet flow rate as dominant drivers; this verbal characterization was considered sufficient for conditional acceptance pending a follow-on structured sensitivity analysis. The package is accepted at Low assurance level with the understanding that hasSensitivityAnalysis linkage and model-form UQ remain outstanding action items for the next assessment cycle.",
